FBIS3-12755 "drnes043_n_94003" FBIS-NES-94-043 Document Type:Daily Report 4 Mar 1994 LEBANON Continued Commentaries, Reports on Church Bombing Judge Appointed To Investigate NC0403123194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1130 GMT 4 Mar 94 NC0403123194 Beirut Radio Lebanon Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] The Higher Judicial Council held a meeting under Judge Philip Khayrallah in al-Yarzah today [Defense Ministry's premises] to evaluate the findings of the security departments concerning the church massacre. Judge Nasri Lahhud, government-appointee to the military court; Judge Tarabay Rahmah, first attorney general for Mount Lebanon; and Riyad Tal'i, first military investigation judge; attended a part of the meeting. After deliberations into the Sayyidat al-Najat Church massacre and reviewing new information, which the conferees unanimously decided to keep secret, the Higher Judicial Council approved a proposal by Justice Minister Bahij Tabbarah to appoint former Prosecutor General Judge Joseph Furayhah as investigating judge into the explosion.
